  "texts": [
    "Figure 7 displays the different image categories.",
    "Accuracy assesmnetIn order to effectively compare the performance of our proposed method to that of other experimental methods [13,[37][38][39][40][41][42][43][44], we opted to utilize the same training-to-test set ratios that were employed in the majority of prior research.",
    "Specifically, we set the training ratios to 80% for the PatternNEt, Eurosat, and RSSCN7 datasets.",
    "This involved randomly selecting images from each dataset to be used for training, with the remaining images being used for testing.",
    "To ensure the accuracy and reliability of our experimental results, we repeated the experiment ten times for each of the three datasets, randomly dividing them according to the training ratios."
  ]
}